<td>Catherine Fitzpatrick<br />(2003–)<sup id="cite_ref-CHA_Heralds_of_Arms_14-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CHA_Heralds_of_Arms-14">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-gazetteCHA_12-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-gazetteCHA-12">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Honorary_positions">Honorary positions</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Canadian_Heraldic_Authority&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Honorary positions"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>The authority also allows for two types of honorary positions: <i>Heralds <a href="/wiki/Emeritus" title="Emeritus">Emeritus</a></i> and <i>Heralds Extraordinary</i>. The emeritus title is reserved for Canadian heralds who have retired;<sup id="cite_ref-CHA_Heralds_Emeritus_17-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CHA_Heralds_Emeritus-17">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup> the title of extraordinary is an honorary position for those who have made notable contributions to heraldry.<sup id="cite_ref-CHA_Heralds_Extraordinary_18-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CHA_Heralds_Extraordinary-18">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup> Honorary heralds can be enlisted by the CHA to perform work for them. Each honorary position grants the individual a badge and a title also based on a Canadian river.
</p>
<dl><dt>Current holders of honorary positions<sup id="cite_ref-CHA_Heralds_Emeritus_17-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CHA_Heralds_Emeritus-17">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-CHA_Heralds_Extraordinary_18-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CHA_Heralds_Extraordinary-18">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup></dt></dl>
